flowRoot.flowPara: This way is more logical; color meanings are consistent with book/chapter bars above, but it lights up the bar more than I would like.
The problem is largely solved if we differentiate between the highlight color and a "recorded" color, but I really want to keep to two non-greycolors.
By only coloring part of the line, we avoid getting too bright without introducing a new color:
